  26class ColumnConfigurations:
  27    """Enums relating to ways a column can be configured/rendered, and also runtime settings like column filtering."""
  28    class Render(Enum):
  29        """Available settings for how a column may be rendered."""
  30        AUTO = "auto"
  31        NUMBER = "number"
  32        DATE = "date"
  33        BOOLEAN = "boolean"
  34        STRING = "string"
  35        VIEW = "view"
  36
  37    class Filter:
  38        """Column filtering settings, including conditions and filter icon visibility"""
  39        class Condition(Enum):
  40            """
  41            This is a complete collection of conditions, but not all conditions are applicable based on the column type.
  42            """
  43            BETWEEN = "between"  # number, NOT date
  44            BETWEEN_DATES = "between dates"
  45            BETWEEN_DATE_TIMES = "between date times"
  46            CONTAINS = "contains"
  47            DATE_EQUALS = "date equals"
  48            DATE_TIME_EQUALS = "date time equals"
  49            EARLIER_THAN_DATE = "earlier than date"
  50            EARLIER_THAN_DATE_TIME = "earlier than date time"
  51            ENDS_WITH = "ends with"  # string
  52            EQUALS = "equals"  # string or number, NOT date
  53            FALSE = "false"
  54            GREATER_THAN = "greater than"
  55            GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUAL_TO = "greater than or equal to"
  56            LATER_THAN_DATE = "later than date"
  57            LATER_THAN_DATE_TIME = "later than date time"
  58            LESS_THAN = "less than"
  59            LESS_THAN_OR_EQUAL_TO = "less than or equal to"
  60            STARTS_WITH = "starts with"  # string
  61            TRUE = "true"
  62
  63        class Visible(Enum):
  64            """Settings for specifying the appearance of the column filter icon in the header."""
  65            ALWAYS = "always"
  66            ON_HOVER = "on-hover"
  67            NEVER = "never"

 102    def cell_is_root_selection(self, row_index: int, column_index: int) -> bool:
 103        """
 104        Determine if the cell of a Table is the root of the current selection.
 105
 106        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row we will check.
 107        :param column_index: The zero-based index of the column we will check.
 108
 109        :returns: True, if the resultant cell is the root of the current selection of the Table.
 110
 111        :raises TimeoutException: If the supplied row and column indices are invalid.
 112        """
 113        _locator = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'{self._ROW_LOCATOR}[data-row-index="{row_index}"] '
 114                                     f'{self._CELL_LOCATOR}[data-column-index="{column_index}"]')
 115        try:
 116            return ComponentPiece(
 117                locator=_locator,
 118                driver=self.driver,
 119                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 120                poll_freq=self.poll_freq).find().find_element(*self._ROOT_SELECTION_LOCATOR) is not None
 121        except StaleElementReferenceException:
 122            return self.cell_is_root_selection(row_index=row_index, column_index=column_index)
 123        except NoSuchElementException:
 124            return False

 126    def cell_is_selected(self, row_index: int, column_index: int) -> bool:
 127        """
 128        Determine if a specified cell is currently part of the active selection of the Table.
 129
 130        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row we will check.
 131        :param column_index: The zero-based index of the column we will check.
 132
 133        :returns: True, if the resultant cell is part of the current selection of the Table.
 134
 135        :raises TimeoutException: If the supplied row and column indices are invalid.
 136        """
 137        _locator = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'{self.__get_row_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)} '
 138                                     f'{self.__get_column_css_by_index(column_index=column_index)}')
 139        try:
 140            return ComponentPiece(
 141                locator=_locator,
 142                driver=self.driver,
 143                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 144                poll_freq=self.poll_freq).find().find_element(*self._SELECTED_CELL_LOCATOR) is not None
 145        except StaleElementReferenceException:
 146            return self.cell_is_root_selection(row_index=row_index, column_index=column_index)
 147        except NoSuchElementException:
 148            return False

 159    def collapse_subview_by_row_index(self, row_index: int) -> None:
 160        """
 161        Collapse an expanded subview. Takes no action if the subview is already collapsed.
 162
 163        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row which might have an expanded subview.
 164
 165        :raises TimeoutException: if no row exists with the supplied index.
 166        """
 167        if self.subview_is_expanded(row_index=row_index):
 168            locator = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, self.__get_subview_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index))
 169            subview_arrow = ComponentPiece(locator=locator, driver=self.driver, parent_locator_list=self.locator_list)
 170            subview_arrow.click(binding_wait_time=0.5)

 228    def expand_subview_by_row_index(self, row_index: int) -> None:
 229        """
 230        Expand the subview of a row of the Table.
 231
 232        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row which contains the subview to be expanded.
 233
 234        :raises TimeoutException: If no row exists with the supplied index.
 235        :raises AssertionError: If the interaction does not result in the subview being expanded.
 236        """
 237        if not self.subview_is_expanded(row_index=row_index):
 238            ComponentPiece(
 239                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, self.__get_subview_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)),

 241                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 242                poll_freq=self.poll_freq)\
 243                .click(binding_wait_time=0.5)
 244        IAAssert.is_true(
 245            value=self.subview_is_expanded(row_index=row_index),
 246            failure_msg=f"Failed to expand a subview for row {row_index}.")

 305    def inclusive_select_cells_by_indices(
 306            self, list_of_row_column_index_tuples: List[Tuple[Union[int, str], Union[int, str]]]) -> None:
 307        """
 308        Select all content between a set of cells. Shift will be held during this event.
 309
 310        :param list_of_row_column_index_tuples: A list of tuples where each tuple contains the zero-based index of the
 311            target row as the 0th element and the zero-based index of the target column as the 1th element.
 312
 313        :raises TimeoutException: If any of the supplied tuples fail to define a valid cell.
 314        """
 315        cell_web_element_list = []
 316        tuple_row_index_location = 0
 317        tuple_column_index_location = 1
 318        for i in range(len(list_of_row_column_index_tuples)):
 319            _row_index = list_of_row_column_index_tuples[i][tuple_row_index_location]
 320            _column_index = list_of_row_column_index_tuples[i][tuple_column_index_location]
 321            _locator = (
 322                By.CSS_SELECTOR,
 323                f'{self.__get_row_css_by_row_index(row_index=_row_index)} '
 324                f'{self.__get_column_css_by_index(column_index=_column_index)}')
 325            cell_web_element_list.append(
 326                ComponentPiece(
 327                    locator=_locator,
 328                    driver=self.driver,
 329                    parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 330                    poll_freq=self.poll_freq).find())
 331            if len(cell_web_element_list) == 1:
 332                cell_web_element_list[0].click()
 333            else:
 334                IASelenium(driver=self.driver).inclusive_multi_select_elements(web_element_list=cell_web_element_list)

 354    def row_is_completely_selected(self, row_index: int) -> bool:
 355        """
 356        Determine if every cell of a row is currently selected.
 357
 358        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row to check.
 359
 360        :returns: True, if every cel within the specified row is currently selected - False otherwise.
 361        """
 362        for i in range(self.get_column_count()):
 363            if not self.cell_is_selected(row_index=row_index, column_index=i):
 364                return False
 365        return True

 367    def rows_are_completely_selected(self, list_of_row_indices: List[Union[int, str]]) -> bool:
 368        """
 369        Determine if a set of rows is completely selected.
 370
 371        :param list_of_row_indices: A list which contains the zero-based indices of al rows to check.
 372
 373        :returns: True, if every row specified in the list is completely selected - False otherwise.
 374
 375        :raises TimeoutException: If any of the specified rows does not exist.
 376        """
 377        for i in range(len(list_of_row_indices)):
 378            if not self.row_is_completely_selected(row_index=i):
 379                return False
 380        return True

 382    def set_cell_data_by_row_index_column_id(
 383            self,
 384            zero_based_row_index: int,
 385            column_id: str,
 386            text: str,
 387            commit_value: bool) -> None:
 388        """
 389        Set the data of a cell specified by a zero-based row index and a CASE-SENSITIVE column ID.
 390
 391        :param zero_based_row_index: The zero-based index of the row you are targeting.
 392        :param column_id: The CASE-SENSITIVE id of the column you are targeting. Note that the id may not be the name
 393            of the column as the id is a direct mapping against the keys of the data in use.
 394        :param text: The new data to be set in the specified cell.
 395        :param commit_value: A boolean flag indicating whether to commit changes immediately or not.
 396            If True, changes will be committed by appending Keys.ENTER to it after setting the cell data.
 397            If False, changes will not be committed, allowing for further modifications before committing.
 398
 399        :raises: TimeoutException: If the cell is not already in an editable state; this function does not prepare the
 400        cell for editing.
 401        """
 402
 403        _locator = (By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'{self.__get_row_css_by_row_index(row_index=zero_based_row_index)} '
 404                                     f'{self.__get_column_css_by_column_id(column_id=column_id)} textarea.ia_textArea')
 405        if commit_value:
 406            text += Keys.ENTER
 407        text_input = CommonTextInput(
 408                locator=_locator,
 409                driver=self.driver,
 410                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 411                poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 412        """
 413        Note:
 414        After using commit changes, set_text will attempt to locate the <textarea> and verify if the text has been 
 415        set. However, the <textarea> disappears after committing the changes, resulting in a TimeoutException.
 416        A TimeoutException before attempting to set the text means the cell is not editable. The TimeoutException 
 417        swallowed while actually setting the cell is the one which is expected due to the <textarea> being removed from 
 418        the DOM.
 419        """
 420        text_input.find()
 421        try:
 422            text_input.set_text(text=text, release_focus=False)
 423        except TimeoutException:
 424            pass

 426    def scroll_to_row(self, row_index: int, align_to_top: bool = False) -> None:
 427        """
 428        Scroll the Table so that the specified row is visible.
 429
 430        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row we will scroll to.
 431        :param align_to_top: If True, we will try to align the row to the Top of the viewport. If False, we will attempt
 432            to align the row to the bottom of the viewport.
 433
 434        :raises TimeoutException: If no row exists with the supplied index.
 435        """
 436        row_index = int(row_index)
 437        rows = ComponentPiece(
 438            locator=self._ROW_GROUP_LOCATOR,
 439            driver=self.driver,
 440            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 441            poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 442        min_index = min([int(row.get_attribute('data-row-index')) for row in rows.find_all()])
 443        max_index = max([int(row.get_attribute('data-row-index')) for row in rows.find_all()])
 444        if min_index > row_index:
 445            self._scroll_to_row(row_index=min_index, align_to_top=False)
 446            self.scroll_to_row(row_index=row_index, align_to_top=align_to_top)
 447        elif max_index < row_index:
 448            self._scroll_to_row(row_index=max_index, align_to_top=True)
 449            self.scroll_to_row(row_index=row_index, align_to_top=align_to_top)
 450        else:
 451            self._scroll_to_row(row_index=row_index, align_to_top=align_to_top)
 452
 453    def subview_is_expanded(self, row_index: int) -> bool:
 454        """
 455        Determine if a subview is expanded for a given row. Only works properly in tables which have virtualization
 456        disabled, or if the row is already in view.
 457
 458        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row to check.
 459        """
 460        try:
 461            return "open" in ComponentPiece(
 462                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, self.__get_subview_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)),
 463                driver=self.driver,
 464                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 465                poll_freq=self.poll_freq).find(wait_timeout=1).get_attribute("class")
 466        except TimeoutException:
 467            return False
 468
 469    def _get_count_of_selected_rows(self) -> int:
 470        """
 471        Obtain a count of rows where at least one cell of the row is selected.
 472        """
 473        try:
 474            count = 0
 475            for row in self._rows.find_all():
 476                try:
 477                    row.find_element(*self._SELECTED_CELL_LOCATOR)
 478                    count += 1
 479                except NoSuchElementException:
 480                    pass
 481            return count
 482        except StaleElementReferenceException:
 483            return self.get_count_of_selected_rows()
 484
 485    def _scroll_to_row(self, row_index: int, align_to_top: bool = False) -> None:
 486        """
 487        Scroll the Table so that the specified row is visible.
 488
 489        :param row_index: The zero-based index of the row we will scroll to.
 490        :param align_to_top: If True, we will try to align the row to the Top of the viewport. If False, we will attempt
 491            to align the row to the bottom of the viewport.
 492
 493        :raises TimeoutException: If no row exists with the supplied index.
 494        """
 495        row = ComponentPiece(
 496            locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, self.__get_row_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)),
 497            driver=self.driver,
 498            parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 499            poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 500        row.scroll_to_element(align_to_top=align_to_top)
 501        row.wait_on_binding()
 502
 503    def __get_column_css_by_index(self, column_index: Union[int, str]) -> str:
 504        """Obtain the CSS which defines a column based on its index."""
 505        return f'{self._CELL_LOCATOR[1]}[data-column-index="{column_index}"]'
 506
 507    def __get_column_css_by_column_id(self, column_id: Union[int, str]) -> str:
 508        """Obtain the CSS which defines a column based on its id."""
 509        return f'{self._CELL_LOCATOR[1]}[data-column-id="{column_id}"]'
 510
 511    def __get_row_css_by_row_index(self, row_index: Union[int, str]) -> str:
 512        """Obtain the CSS which defines a row based on its index."""
 513        return f'{self._ROW_GROUP_LOCATOR[1]}[data-row-index="{row_index}"] {self._ROW_LOCATOR[1]}'
 514
 515    def __get_subview_css_by_row_index(self, row_index: Union[int, str]) -> str:
 516        """Obtain the CSS which defines a subview based on the index of the row which contains it."""
 517        return f'{self.__get_row_css_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)} {self._SUBVIEW_ARROW_CSS}'

 646    def _get_filter_by_column_index(self, column_index: int) -> ComponentPiece:
 647        """
 648        Obtain the filter piece of the column with the specified index.
 649        """
 650        filter_comp = self._filter_cells.get(column_index)
 651        if not filter_comp:
 652            filter_comp = ComponentPiece(
 653                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "div.filter-button svg"),
 654                driver=self.driver,
 655                parent_locator_list=self._get_header_cell_by_index(column_index=column_index).locator_list,
 656                wait_timeout=1)
 657            self._filter_cells[column_index] = filter_comp
 658        return filter_comp

 660    def _get_filter_icon_by_column_index(self, column_index: Union[int, str]) -> ComponentPiece:
 661        """
 662        Obtain the icon of the filter for a column by providing the column index.
 663        """
 664        return ComponentPiece(
 665            locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "path.iaFilterIcon"),
 666            driver=self.driver,
 667            parent_locator_list=self._get_filter_by_column_index(column_index=column_index).locator_list)
 668
 669    def _get_header_row_group(
 670            self,
 671            zero_based_header_row_group_index: Optional[Union[int, str]] = 0) -> ComponentPiece:
 672        """
 673        Obtain a Header Row Group of varying specificity, based on the supplied arguments.
 674
 675        :param zero_based_header_row_group_index: The 0-based index of the Header Row Group. If None is supplied, then
 676            all row groups will be matched.
 677
 678        :returns: A ComponentPiece which defines the Header Group entry with varying levels of specificity; the more
 679            information supplied, the more specific the locator will be.
 680        """
 681        index = str(zero_based_header_row_group_index) \
 682            if zero_based_header_row_group_index is not None else zero_based_header_row_group_index
 683        header_row_group = self._header_row_groups.get(index)
 684        if not header_row_group:
 685            row_index_piece = f'[data-row-index="{index}"]' if index is not None else ''
 686            header_row_group = ComponentPiece(
 687                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'{self._HEADER_GROUP_LOCATOR[1]}{row_index_piece}'),
 688                driver=self.driver,
 689                parent_locator_list=self.locator_list,
 690                description=f"The {zero_based_header_row_group_index}th row of Header Row Groups.",
 691                poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 692            self._header_row_groups[index] = header_row_group
 693        return header_row_group
 694
 695    def _get_cell_from_header_row_group(
 696            self,
 697            label: str,
 698            zero_based_header_row_group_index: Optional[Union[int, str]] = 0):
 699        index = str(zero_based_header_row_group_index) \
 700            if zero_based_header_row_group_index is not None else zero_based_header_row_group_index
 701        cell = self._header_row_group_cells.get((index, label))
 702        if not cell:
 703            cell = ComponentPiece(
 704                locator=(By.CSS_SELECTOR, f'div.tc[data-label="{label}"]'),
 705                driver=self.driver,
 706                parent_locator_list=self._get_header_row_group(
 707                    zero_based_header_row_group_index=zero_based_header_row_group_index).locator_list,
 708                description=f"A Header Row Group cell in the {zero_based_header_row_group_index}th row, with a "
 709                            f"label of '{label}'.",
 710                poll_freq=self.poll_freq)
 711            self._header_row_group_cells[(index, label)] = cell
 712        return cell

1467    def remove_column_filter(self, column_index: int) -> None:
1468        """
1469        Remove the applied filter for a column.
1470
1471        :param column_index: The zero-based index of the column for which we wil remove the applied filter.
1472
1473        :raises TimeoutException: If the column is not configured to have any filtering done.
1474        :raises AssertionError: If unable to successfully remove any filter from the column.
1475        """
1476        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1477            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1478            self.click_filter_for_column(column_index=column_index)
1479        try:
1480            self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1481        except ElementClickInterceptedException:
1482            selenium = IASelenium(driver=self.driver)
1483            original_height = selenium.get_inner_height()
1484            selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=float(original_height) + 50)
1485            try:
1486                self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1487            finally:
1488                selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=original_height)
1489        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1490            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1491        IAAssert.is_not_true(
1492            value=self._header.column_has_active_filter_applied(column_index=column_index),
1493            failure_msg=f"Failed to remove column filter for column {column_index}.")
1494

1094    def get_displayed_row_data_as_a_list_of_dictionaries(
1095            self, start_row_index: Optional[int] = None, end_row_index: Optional[int] = None) -> List[dict]:
1096        """
1097        Obtain the data of a subset of rows.
1098
1099        :param start_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the beginning of the subset. If not
1100            supplied, we will begin with the 0th row.
1101        :param end_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the end of the subset. if not supplied,
1102            we will end with the last row.
1103
1104        :returns: A list of dictionaries, where the keys of each dictionary match the columns ids.
1105
1106        :raises IndexError: If the supplied row indices are invalid based on the data.
1107        """
1108        return [
1109            self.get_row_data_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)
1110            for row_index in range(self.get_count_of_rows())
1111        ][start_row_index:end_row_index]

1468    def remove_column_filter(self, column_index: int) -> None:
1469        """
1470        Remove the applied filter for a column.
1471
1472        :param column_index: The zero-based index of the column for which we wil remove the applied filter.
1473
1474        :raises TimeoutException: If the column is not configured to have any filtering done.
1475        :raises AssertionError: If unable to successfully remove any filter from the column.
1476        """
1477        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1478            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1479            self.click_filter_for_column(column_index=column_index)
1480        try:
1481            self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1482        except ElementClickInterceptedException:
1483            selenium = IASelenium(driver=self.driver)
1484            original_height = selenium.get_inner_height()
1485            selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=float(original_height) + 50)
1486            try:
1487                self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1488            finally:
1489                selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=original_height)
1490        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1491            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1492        IAAssert.is_not_true(
1493            value=self._header.column_has_active_filter_applied(column_index=column_index),
1494            failure_msg=f"Failed to remove column filter for column {column_index}.")

1094    def get_displayed_row_data_as_a_list_of_dictionaries(
1095            self, start_row_index: Optional[int] = None, end_row_index: Optional[int] = None) -> List[dict]:
1096        """
1097        Obtain the data of a subset of rows.
1098
1099        :param start_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the beginning of the subset. If not
1100            supplied, we will begin with the 0th row.
1101        :param end_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the end of the subset. if not supplied,
1102            we will end with the last row.
1103
1104        :returns: A list of dictionaries, where the keys of each dictionary match the columns ids.
1105
1106        :raises IndexError: If the supplied row indices are invalid based on the data.
1107        """
1108        return [
1109            self.get_row_data_by_row_index(row_index=row_index)
1110            for row_index in range(self.get_count_of_rows())
1111        ][start_row_index:end_row_index]

Obtain the data of a subset of rows.

  • start_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the beginning of the subset. If not supplied, we will begin with the 0th row.
  • end_row_index: The zero-based index of the row which defines the end of the subset. if not supplied, we will end with the last row.

def remove_column_filter(self, column_index: int) -> None: 
1468    def remove_column_filter(self, column_index: int) -> None:
1469        """
1470        Remove the applied filter for a column.
1471
1472        :param column_index: The zero-based index of the column for which we wil remove the applied filter.
1473
1474        :raises TimeoutException: If the column is not configured to have any filtering done.
1475        :raises AssertionError: If unable to successfully remove any filter from the column.
1476        """
1477        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1478            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1479            self.click_filter_for_column(column_index=column_index)
1480        try:
1481            self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1482        except ElementClickInterceptedException:
1483            selenium = IASelenium(driver=self.driver)
1484            original_height = selenium.get_inner_height()
1485            selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=float(original_height) + 50)
1486            try:
1487                self._filter_modal.click_remove_filter()
1488            finally:
1489                selenium.set_inner_window_dimensions(inner_height=original_height)
1490        if not self.column_filter_modal_is_displayed():
1491            self.hover_over_column_header(column_index=column_index)
1492        IAAssert.is_not_true(
1493            value=self._header.column_has_active_filter_applied(column_index=column_index),
1494            failure_msg=f"Failed to remove column filter for column {column_index}.")
